                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <desc>Prayer of <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወልደ፡ ብርሃን፡</foreign>, <locus target="#155v" facs="158"/>
                           </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc>Overlooked words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#2v #8r #12r #13r #21v #41v" facs="005 010 014 015 024 044"/>, etc.);
                        and overlooked lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#98r #103r #136r #155r" facs="100 105 138 157"/>)</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc>
                          The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an appropriate aspect ratio
                          for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe completes the line of text above the end of the line (throughout).
                          This scribe will also reduce the font size at the end of lines to avoid having to go onto the next line (e.g., <locus target="#8v #9v #10v #14v #15v" facs="011 012 013 017 018"/>, etc.)
                        </desc>
                        </item>

                        <item xml:id="e4">
                           <desc>The general condition of the vellum is a bit dirty and stained but relatively unworn. Many folios are water stained around the perimeter and the text is smudged</desc>
                        </item>
